prompt:
Deploy github-relay on classic-laddie and configure it to forward GitHub webhook events to klaus.

## What to do

### 1. Add github-relay flake input (flake.nix)
Add alongside the existing reel-life input:
```nix
github-relay = {
  url = "github:patflynn/github-relay";
  inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
};
```

### 2. Import the module (hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix)
Add to the imports list alongside the existing reel-life module:
```nix
inputs.github-relay.nixosModules.default
```

### 3. Configure the service (hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix)
Add the github-relay service configuration:
```nix
services.github-relay = {
  enable = true;
  port = 8077;
  webhookSecretFile = config.age.secrets.github-webhook-secret.path;

  funnel = {
    enable = true;
  };

  consumers = {
    # Forward all PR/CI events to klaus dashboard
    klaus = {
      repo = "*";
      events = [ "push" "check_run" "check_suite" "pull_request" "pull_request_review" ];
      action = "http";
      url = "http://localhost:9800/webhook/github";
    };
  };
};
```

### 4. Add the webhook secret (agenix)
Add a new secret for the GitHub webhook:

In secrets/secrets.nix, add:
```nix
"github-webhook-secret.age".publicKeys = keys.users ++ keys.hosts;
```

In hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix, add the age secret definition alongside the existing ones:
```nix
age.secrets."github-webhook-secret" = {
  file = ../../secrets/github-webhook-secret.age;
  mode = "0400";
};
```

### 5. Update flake.lock
Run: nix flake update github-relay

### 6. Verify the build
Run: nix build .#nixosConfigurations.classic-laddie.config.system.build.toplevel --dry-run
or: nix flake check

## Important notes
- DO NOT create the actual .age secret file (that requires the user's age key)
- The github-relay module requires tsnsrv/tailscale for funnel support — check if that's already configured on classic-laddie. If not, the funnel option may need to be disabled or tsnsrv needs to be added.
- Look at how other services are configured in the host file for patterns to follow
- The webhook secret file path uses agenix — follow the same pattern as reel-life-telegram-token and other existing secrets
